---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'; import versions from '../../data/methodology/versions.json';
---
<BaseLayout title="Methodology | CourtScope"><section class="section"><div class="shell"><p class="eyebrow">Transparent by design</p><h1>Methodology</h1><div class="notice warning"><strong>No validated production methodology exists in this phase.</strong> The current version is a fixture contract for interface and storage testing only.</div><div class="grid grid-2"><div><h2>How the future score will work</h2><p>CourtScope will estimate adjusted racial disparity in aggregate sentencing outcomes while controlling for supported case differences. A higher score will mean lower measured disparity, not proof of perfect fairness or intent.</p><ol><li>Define qualifying cases and court-specific cohorts.</li><li>Validate source coverage and judge identity.</li><li>Model supported sentencing outcomes with regression.</li><li>Run matching or weighting sensitivity checks.</li><li>Measure uncertainty and model stability.</li><li>Publish only when hard sufficiency gates pass.</li></ol></div><div class="card"><h2>Publication gates</h2><ul><li>At least 50 qualifying cases</li><li>Supported subgroup minimums</li><li>Acceptable uncertainty width</li><li>Source and field coverage</li><li>Stable identity and model behavior</li><li>No unresolved provenance or privacy conflict</li></ul></div></div><h2>Versions</h2><div class="table-wrap"><table><thead><tr><th>Version</th><th>Status</th><th>Released</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody>{versions.versions.map(v=><tr><td>{v.version}</td><td>{v.status}</td><td>{v.released}</td><td>{v.notes}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table></div></div></section></BaseLayout>
